  <article id="about-article-JR77M4X9" class="about_pub-article">
    <h1>Om</h1>
    Undlien gjennomførte ein studie for å utforske korleis sosiale entreprenørar kan nytte store idrettsarrangement, som Ungdoms-OL i Lillehammer, til å fremje prosjekta sine. Ved å intervjue fem prosjektleiarar fann dei at arrangementet gav betydelige moglegheiter for nettverksbygging og etablering av sosiale forbindelsar. Desse forbindelsane, kjent som sosial kapital, er avgjerande for å skape sosial verdi og gagn for ulike grupper. Kultur- og utdanningsprogrammet (CEP) ved leikane var spesielt nyttig i denne samanhengen. Denne studien bidreg til forståinga av korleis idrettsarrangement kan utnyttast for sosialt entreprenørskap, og gir innsikt i potensialet for å skape positiv sosial påverknad gjennom idrett.
  </article>
  <article id="keywords-article-JR77M4X9" class="keywords-article">

  <article id="abstract-article-JR77M4X9" class="abstract-article">
    <h1>Samandrag</h1>
    The aim of this article is to examine the possibilities that social entrepreneurs have for using a major sports event as an arena for their work. A case study using five different project leaders of social entrepreneurial projects were undertaken and qualitative interviews about their experiences and perceptions related to using the Youth Olympic Games in Lillehammer (LYOG) as an advantage for their cause, were conducted. The LYOG was considered a big entrepreneurial opportunity by the project leaders, especially for networking and improving bonding social capital and with several possibilities for creating social value for different groups, especially due to the Culture and Education Program (CEP). Theoretically, this article seeks to contribute to the field of sports entrepreneurship, social entrepreneurship and social capital in a sports context.
  </article>
